The South African Weather Service has warned of severe thunderstorms over the western parts of KZN and Midlands on Monday evening. The weather office said it expects conditions which will result in showers and thundershowers with some of the thunderstorms becoming severe and accompanied by hail, heavy downpours, strong damaging winds and excessive lightning. Heavy downpours may lead to localised flooding of roads and low-lying bridges. Areas expected to be affected include Alfred Duma - Indaka, Alfred Duma - Ladysmith, Dannhauser, Dr N. Dlamini-Zuma - Underberg, eMadlangeni, Endumeni and Newcastle.